ksdk:manifest.name: SDK version 2.3.1 package for MK22FX512Axxx12 device
ksdk:manifest.brief: This is SDK version 2.3.1 manifest file. It describes the content of the SDK version 2.3.1 package for MK22FX512Axxx12 device and additional settings for tools that support SDK version 2.3.1

board.name: TWR-K21F120M
board.description: TWR-K21F120MA: TWR-K21F120MA: Kinetis K21 120 MHz Tower System Module

specific.content:
The TWR-K21F120MA is a development board for the Kinetis® K21 and K22 120 MHz 32-bit ARM® Cortex®-M4 MCUs with floating point unit.
The board provides rapid prototyping for applications requiring high feature integration, as low as 240uA/MHz low-power consumption and mid/high flash memory density (up to 1 MB) that need to support multiple communication stacks.

device.name: MK21FA12
device.description: K21_120: Kinetis K21-120 MHZ, Full-Speed USB, Anti-Tamper Microcontrollers based on ARM® Cortex®-M4

specific.content:
The Kinetis K21 120 MHz MCU family targets cost-sensitive applications requiring low-power functionality.
  • Features hardware encryption and tamper detection
  • Includes a rich suite of analog, communication, timing and control peripherals to accommodate a wide range of requirements
  • Maximizes board space and enhances performance with minimum-length interconnections
  • Provides performance efficiency with industry-leading low power
  • Delivers significant BOM savings through smart on-chip integration
  • Shares the comprehensive enablement and scalability of the Kinetis portfolio

device.name: MK22FA12
device.description: K22_120: Kinetis® K22-120 MHz, Cost Effective, Full-Speed USB Microcontrollers (MCUs) based on ARM® Cortex®-M4 Core

specific.content:
Kinetis® K22 MCUs have been optimized for cost-sensitive applications requiring low power flexibility and processing efficiency.
  • Delivers industry-leading low power while providing significant bill-of-materials savings through smart on-chip integration
  • Includes options that support crystal-less USB design for reduced system cost and board space
  • Provides scalability with various levels of integration, offering a rich suite of analog, communication, timing and control peripherals to accommodate a wide range of requirements
  • Shares the comprehensive enablement and scalability of the Kinetis portfolio
